Comment:
I just wanna vent out my Heather story since I've never told anyone before. 
She was the girl I discovered about my sexuality, I've never liked anyone for long and she hit me hard, probably the hardest. She was introvert and I was extrovert,  she was a serious and cold person while i was a pure dork and hugger one, she was the smartest in class while I used to fail every subject,  yet i still fell for her so hard. But I knew that not only she was still in the closet but she was already in love with another girl, a girl that had everything she wanted and everything I lacked, and I hate myself bc I always knew that, and I always knew she wouldn't like me back. I tried to forget her I even tried dating a guy, but i ended up throwing up the first day I dated him bc I didn't like it at all, just by seeing one picture of her even if it was a blurry stupid one I felt so happy, so even if I knew I shouldn't I still tried to spend any opportunity I could to be with her, but lil by lil I realised how lil she cared about me and how much she loved her and that I was just an obstacle between them. Then something happened that really marked me, I decided to close all contacts with her and after nearly 2 years of that stupid one sided love I'm finally starting to move on, prob will get a girlfriend soon too <3

Wanna hear my heather story? Hear we go.

I fell hard for my friend “S.” She was my friend and I was pretty sure she was straight. Because of that, I tried hard to kill the little crush. Then eventually that crush lasted for a year, and it might sound a little silly, but I would always get little panics when ever I saw her. Seeing her everyday would make it worth it to go through the school day, even to go outside. Even when she wasn’t around it would still be worth because the day I saw her like that, it felt like the world was a better place to be in. S is probably not even very attractive in the public’s eye. Or wasn’t even very popular, or extroverted.

And that’s where heather comes in. Heather was the childhood best friend to her, and I couldn’t interfere whenever she was around. Heather was much more sweeter, prettier, and much closer to S than I was. Heather had lots of friends for her kindness, and compared to her world, I was a problem. I remember every time I would hang out with S, she would have this passive aggressive vibe when she came to chat. Eventually S talking to me would be heather talking to S. And I was kicked out. But recently, I’ve been doing better! I feel like I’ve became closer with S and all of my friends. So S, if you are reading this. Thank you so much.

Comment: I actually really love this. Someone commented that they think this is him expressing his femininity through the way he dresses, but I see it a lot differently. The entire song is about wanting to be more like a specific girl to appeal to another person. You can see him gradually dress more femininely throughout the video, wearing gender neutral clothes, adding a hair clip, wearing a skirt, lots of shots with his long hair, etc. All the scenes where he's looking in the mirror, holding an obviously feminine hand to him, and generally engaging in acts that show him trying to perceive himself and have other perceive him as feminine show that he was trying to change his entire self for them. I could 100% be wrong but either way it was beautiful and absolute art.

A little story time:
I had gone for a tour in my country and when I went to my hotel, there was this guy who started singing Heather while coming down the staircase and I was just in front of the staircase and when I realised he was singing Heather, I started singing Heather too and he stopped singing and looked at me and smiled. I smiled back and we started laughing. After a while, when I was going for my dinner, he was singing again and I saw him and said him that he sang really well and he smiled again. He said "when you come after your dinner, we sing many songs, Heather too" And I literally had butterflies in my stomach and we sang Heather together after dinner. 
He was really cutee and he still talks to me. 
In short, Conan Gray, your songs connects people and also makes them happy. So please keep making more songs and I hope they are blockbusters and I will always love you and your songs! Thank you su much!! We love you always♥

You say you guys are like siblings. I believe you’d never go after him. I don’t know about him though. He just looks at you different. Even if your life isn't going the way you want it to right now, I know that you'll be able to make it out alright. I want you to do me a favor. I know I'm just a stranger, but just trust me, okay? Every time you see your reflection, be it in the mirror in the bathroom, in a window somewhere, or in a puddle on the street, I want you to look at yourself and give yourself a hug. Because even if you aren't the prettiest or the smartest or the funniest, you're something that no one else can be: you. And you are the greatest thing you can be. Smile at strangers. Be confident in yourself. Cry when you feel like crying, laugh when you feel like laughing. Treat yourself like a god/goddess because you deserve it. Hold your head up and keep your heart open. You're worth everything and then some. And always remember that no matter what, even if it doesn't seem like it, you're everything to someone. I wanted to make sure no one felt upset like I did - hating myself and crying to sleep. You are all special <3

I just wanna share my story about a "Heather" that I know.
This Heather is my best friend in highschool. She's kind, pretty, cheerful, smart, could sing, she could do almost everything. She was almost perfect. Everyone loved her. As her best friend since birth, am I jealous ? Sometimes, but I'm happy for her as long as it doesn't bother her. One night she messaged me and said "All of this can't make me love myself. Thank you and sorry" and that was the last thing she said to me. She died because of suicide that night. She was perfect even some girls wanted to live as her. But inside, she's broken and all those attention or perfectness she got can't bring her to loving herself and giving herself some happiness.
So why am I telling you this ?? She made me learn that everything is just equal. She have something that I don't have and I also have something that she doesn't have. So what I want to say is, you're okay the way you are. You are handsome, pretty, gorgeous the way you are. And you should be grateful for what you have. And also, you have to learn love yourself first if you want someone to love you.

Comment:
i have a story, for anyone that wants to hear it. this is about my best friend and massive lifelong crush.

let's call my friend "H".

so, we met in 2nd grade when she moved to my school (in Kentucky) from Hawaii. at the time i had a different friend, let's call her "C". so, me and C had been friends since kindergarten. i knew that C was going to go into homeschooling at the end of the year, so i was feeling really sad and tried to make some new friends. at first i hated H because i thought she was trying to steal C from me. but after a while me, C, and H became a group. as it neared the end of the year, i met this random boy, we will call him "B". so, when i met B i didn't know what to think because i had only had female friends before this. i started to develop feelings for B. B didn't like my other friends, so i wasn't sure how to feel or what to do since i had to choose between B (who i fell really hard for), or C and H. it was the end of second grade, and me and H said our last goodbyes to C. we never saw C again. in 3rd grade, ms and H were in different classes. me and B were in the same class again. me and B had other friends (which aren't important enough to name.) and at this point i had H, and me and B's friend group. B hated H. i ended up telling H about my feelings for B. then i told a few other people. as expected, B found out. B started to drift away from me, and those other friends followed. i tried to talk to B but he didn't want anything to do with me. by the end of the year, all i had was H. then the year ended. when 4th grade started, i was still heartbroken over B. B thought i was weird and hated me at this point. H told me she had something to tell me. H told me that she was moving schools and probably wouldn't be seeing me in 5th grade. i was heartbroken. H was all i had, and we still talked about C sometimes, and finding C. it was the end of the fourth grade year. me and H said our final goodbyes, and i was on my own. when 5th grade started, i found out that B was going to the same middle school as me. to be honest, at this point i was pretty much a stalker. i could understand why he would hate me now, because i started to be obsessive, but, you know, first loves, amirite? but seriously, i was so excited. over the years everyone at my elementary had found out about my crush, and since middle school was starting, it would be a secret again, right. yep. too much of a secret. i did my whole sixth grade year virtual and thought of it as the perfect opportunity to escape my feelings for B. nope. actually, more of a chance to embrace them. i know this sounds dumb, but i would just stare at his black zoom box with his name. goofy smile on my face,  just remembering. over the years i had faked so many crushes to try and get away from this one, and i was just thinking how bad of a stalker i was to B. he was introvert, and i am (and have always been) extrovert. to try and distract myself from this crush, i emailed my old friend, H. I didn't know if that email even worked anymore, but surprise. i got an email back. she told me her discord, and i told her mine. we stayed in contact ever since. now, i had another problem. i had an online friend, E, who introduced me to her online friend, R. me and E didn't really contact anymore, and me and R became closer. eventually, i caught feelings for R so i confessed to her. she said she liked me, too, and i thought i escaped. i introduced H to R and R hated H. R brainwashed me into thinking H didn't care about me. it was just me and R now. but at the end of my 6th grade year i found out i needed to go to summer school. i got my phone taken until i finished it. (mind you, me and R had made plans to literally live together and get married in the future btw. by this time i had forgotten about B. i was in summer school, doing my work, yk, as it goes. when i finished, though, everything changed. i went to text R and tell her i was done, but what i opened her contact to was crushing. "i got a girlfriend 2 weeks ago and i was scared to tell you so i dont have a crush on you anymore." that's it. we got into a massive argument, i ended up cutting off all contact with her. i was alone again. everything had gotten so bad. i started thinking about B again. how had an innocent little childhood crush turned into this? i was so mad at myself for letting it get this out of control. i didn't like his as much, but memories, you know?  by the start of 7th grade, i had stopped thinking about him. my friendship with H had been revived, but H wasn't the same, sweet, loving soul. H is now just kinda depressed, i'm sure. H went to visit her grandma in SC right as covid started and is now stuck with her, so now lives there. i'm not the same either, though, so i can't complain. i have new friendships now, and my life is starting to look up. i'm homeschooled, but in the time that i was going to  in-person, i made a decent best friend (lets call them "G") me and G are always talking and laughing, and it's the healthiest friendship i've had in my whole life. i know that i've escaped my crush on B, and i know this sounds stupid, but it kinda saved me. because obsessing over someone who you haven't spoken to in 4 years isn't healthy. anyways, 7th grade ends in May 2022, and i'm the happiest i've been in a long time. 







TL:DR 

my crush that i chased around my whole life and the story of all my greatest (and worst) friendships. my story.

Video Description: Official music video by Conan Gray performing "Heather” Conan's debut album "Kid Krow" available everywhere now: https://ConanGray.lnk.to/KidKrow Connect ...
Comment:
okay hear me out:

I think he already explained, what the song is about and most of the lyrics are quite self-explainatory. but I feel like "I wish I were heather" doesn´t necessarly ONLY mean that he simply wants to be the girl named heather, that the person, who he is in love with is dating. but I think the fact that heather is a girl could be THE important aspect.

I feel like the song could also be about the wish of expressing yourself in a way that society would normally not accept. The "old society norms" are things like "girls wear dresses, have long hair and act in a certain feminine way". In comparision to that boys should be strong, not show many emotions, wear pants, have short hair etc. . 
The sentence "I wish I were heather" could be conan´s wish of getting out of these norms. that boys wearing dresses and skirts should be normalized. That it should be a normal thing for people who identify as masculine (and everyone else) to act in a way that society sees as feminine today. To normalize boys having long hair and not telling them that that´s a "girly" thing.

In the end of the music video he is wearing a skirt, a hair clip and his hair is (obviously) long. He then takes a photo and uploads it onto social media. he shows the world how he wants to express himself. he makes it a public thing and at the same time, without really doing it on purpose, he says that he doesn´t want to be judged. everyone should have the ability to express themselves the way they want to without getting judged.

thank you for coming to my ted talk ^^

also to make things clear, this is just a theory, that came to my mind while watching this video, so don´t hate thank you :)

This is so random but I feel like some people may need to hear some reasons why you should stay alive.

1. We would miss you. 

2. It's not worth the regret. Either by yourself if you failed or just simply left scars, or the regret everyone else feels by not doing enough to help you. 

3. It does get better. Believe it or not it will eventually get better. Sometimes you have to go through the storm to get to the rainbow. 

4. There's so much you would miss out on doing. 

5. There is always a reason to live. It might not be clear right now, but it is always there. 

6. So many people care, and it would hurt them if you hurt yourself. 

7. You ARE worth it. Don't let anyone, especially yourself, tell you otherwise. 

8. You are amazing. 

9. A time will come, once you've battled the toughest times of your life and are in ease once again, where you will be so glad that you decided to keep on living. You will emerge stronger from this all, and won't regret your choice to carry on with life. Because things always get better. 

10. What about all the things you've always wanted to do? What about the things you've planned, but never got around to doing? You can't do them when you're dead. 

11. I love you. Even if only one person loves you, that's still a reason to stay alive. 

12. You won't be able to listen to music if you die. 

13. Killing yourself is never worth it. You'll hurt both yourself and all the people you care about. 

14. There are so many people that would miss you, including me. 

15. You're preventing a future generation, YOUR KIDS, from even being born. 

16. How do you think your family would feel? Would it improve their lives if you died? 

17. You're gorgeous, amazing, and to someone you are perfect. 

18. Think about your favourite music artist, you'll never hear their voice again... 

19. You'll never have the feeling of walking into a warm building on a cold day 

20. Listening to incredibly loud music 

21. Being alive is just really good. 

22. Not being alive is really bad.

24. Red pandas
